      <div class="msgContentFrame"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cW-dfDTruMQ" title="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cW-dfDTruMQ" rel="external nofollow">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cW-dfDTruMQ</a> <br /> <br />Take special notice to the cities, naming the NPC carrying on about a daily life.  Now look at the actual in game cities and notice how lifeless it is.  Now look back at another SE MMO called FFXI and notice how much life the nations had inside their walls. <br /> <br />FFXIV needs NPC with feeling; lives to live and stories to tell.  They should tell us about Eorzea, it's history and current settings.  I can honestly say I have no idea what Eorzea is about outside the main storyline.  I don't feel I should log onto a website and read pages to understand what makes the world tick.  I learned everything about FFXI in the game and want to do the same in FFXIV. <br /> <br />I guess this follows hand in hand with NPC that give out story quest and I think this one key feature that is lacking in FFXIV to make it a true success.  Sure Guildleve take care of the repeatable grind quest but it needs more, well life. <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>FFXIV Dyvid Pandemoniumm ~ Palamecia <br />FFXI Dyvid ~ Pandemonium (Retired)</div></div>
