      <div class="msgContentFrame">For me, its not so much the lack of players in the outlying areas, its the lack of npc's or monsters or w/e. I want to feel the vastness of the world, which I do, but I don't want the empty feeling this game also has. I remember the first time I explored Coerthas, I'm up high and looking around, the view was incredible. I loved the fact that I wasn't running into a ton of players, but then I was starting to realize how empty the whole area was. I found what looked to be a fort or something, found a couple of them to be exact. I thought it was cool, that it might be an outpost or something. Once I get there, I start to think that the place was abandoned a long time ago during the war. There was damage to the stone walkways and all that. But what didn't make any sense, if this place was long abandoned, were the lit brazers. There was nobody there, but there were lit fires. I was expecting people to be there. I was hoping in my travels I would run across a lone cabin or a traveling merchant, something to give this game more life.  <br /> <br />Its hard for me to exactly pinpoint it, but this game is lacking life, I'll know it when the games starts to have it though lol. About the bazaars, I'm sure its like some of the other places I have run across. The content hasn't been added to those places and I'm sure that you can't do anything there right now, no matter what your level is. I noticed that some of them have guild signs. One place had one for alchemy, but you couldn't go inside or anything.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/557565.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></div></div>
